not support his dream.

857
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:09,159
You're just afraid he

858
00:39:09,159 --> 00:39:11,159
might lose interest quickly and not persevere,

859
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:11,800
right?

860
00:39:12,840 --> 00:39:13,519
That's not it.

861
00:39:14,039 --> 00:39:15,199
I don't support him

862
00:39:15,519 --> 00:39:17,320
thinking that because he can strum a guitar

863
00:39:17,599 --> 00:39:18,760
and hum a few songs,

864
00:39:19,079 --> 00:39:20,639
then he can succeed.

865
00:39:21,639 --> 00:39:23,159
We're just ordinary folks.

866
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,559
How can we afford to chase

867
00:39:24,559 --> 00:39:25,880
something that's like

868
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:27,400
a million soldiers crossing a single log bridge?

869
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:28,480
No.

870
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:29,639
Then how do you plan

871
00:39:29,639 --> 00:39:31,000
to realize your dream?

872
00:39:31,199 --> 00:39:31,679
Well...

873
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:35,079
Once I get there,

874
00:39:35,079 --> 00:39:37,280
I think there will naturally be a way.

875
00:39:38,199 --> 00:39:39,679
Alright, so then,

876
00:39:40,159 --> 00:39:41,400
let me help you calculate

877
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:43,159
the cost of your "distance."

878
00:39:43,159 --> 00:39:43,679
Okay.
Let's take Mr. Chen

879
00:39:44,519 --> 00:39:45,400
as an example.

880
00:39:46,159 --> 00:39:47,440
In Hangzhou,

881
00:39:47,440 --> 00:39:48,480
his monthly rent

882
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:49,760
is two thousand eight hundred yuan.

883
00:39:50,079 --> 00:39:51,679
And that's sharing with someone.

884
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:54,840
His daily food expenses are about

885
00:39:55,159 --> 00:39:56,039
thirty to forty yuan.

886
00:39:56,239 --> 00:39:57,320
And that's with the subsidy

887
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:58,239
from our firm.

888
00:39:58,599 --> 00:39:59,960
Without the subsidy,

889
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:01,519
just casually ordering takeout

890
00:40:01,519 --> 00:40:02,400
or eating out,

891
00:40:02,639 --> 00:40:03,880
the monthly food cost

892
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:05,280
would exceed two thousand yuan.

893
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:08,079
On top of that, there are utilities,

894
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:10,119
transportation, and communication costs.

895
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:12,880
When you're away from home,
you don't have health insurance.

896
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:14,960
If you get sick,

897
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:16,559
you'll have medical expenses.

898
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:19,519
If you can't even eat well,

899
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:20,880
or can't afford to get sick,

900
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:22,400
how can you realize

901
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:23,840
your own musical dream?

902
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,280
Actually, dreaming is easy,

903
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:28,480
but realizing a dream is hard.

904
00:40:30,559 --> 00:40:31,440
So,

905
00:40:32,119 --> 00:40:33,239
are you mentally prepared

906
00:40:33,679 --> 00:40:34,880
and financially prepared?

907
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:36,679
What preparation does he have?

908
00:40:36,880 --> 00:40:38,519
He lacks both talent and effort.

909
00:40:39,079 --> 00:40:40,480
I am planning for my son.

910
00:40:40,599 --> 00:40:41,320
I'm not wrong.

911
00:40:43,079 --> 00:40:44,280
Of course, you're not wrong.

912
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:48,599
I also understand that "parents' love for their child

913
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:50,119
plans far ahead."

914
00:40:51,079 --> 00:40:51,960
Your intentions

915
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,239
are certainly for his good.

916
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:55,079
But I also think,

917
00:40:55,679 --> 00:40:57,000
you have your reasons,

918
00:40:57,239 --> 00:40:58,199
and Li Shishan

919
00:40:58,440 --> 00:40:59,840
has his own reasons too.

920
00:41:01,079 --> 00:41:01,840
Don't you think

921
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:03,239
we could perhaps
put ourselves in each other's shoes

922
00:41:04,599 --> 00:41:06,239
to reach a better consensus?

923
00:41:06,679 --> 00:41:07,800
What reasons does he have?

924
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:08,960
You tell me.

925
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:12,920
Actually, Shishan's situation

926
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:14,840
reminds me

927
00:41:15,199 --> 00:41:15,920
of when I first

928
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:17,119
decided to write novels.

929
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:18,599
Back then,

930
00:41:18,599 --> 00:41:20,440
my parents didn't support it either.

931
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:22,719
They thought it was hard to succeed,

932
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:23,639
unstable.

933
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:25,800
But I still

934
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:28,159
stuck with it stubbornly.

935
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:29,280
I thought at the time,

936
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:30,920
at worst I'll hit a dead end,

937
00:41:31,039 --> 00:41:31,920
but at least I tried,
and I wouldn't regret it.

938
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:34,519
As it turned out, unexpectedly,

939
00:41:34,880 --> 00:41:36,519
I've kept writing until now.

940
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:38,480
And now,

941
00:41:38,480 --> 00:41:38,960
I've also found
more of this profession's

942
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:40,760
value and meaning.

943
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:44,159
When I see the words I've written

944
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:45,599
can bring

945
00:41:45,599 --> 00:41:47,119
positive energy to people,

946
00:41:47,119 --> 00:41:48,400
I'm truly very grateful

947
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:48,960
that I made the decision back then,

948
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,039
regardless of the consequences.

949
00:41:55,079 --> 00:41:56,440
Actually, we, as children,

950
00:41:57,199 --> 00:41:58,440
are very grateful for our parents' guidance

951
00:41:58,440 --> 00:41:59,239
and direction.

952
00:42:00,159 --> 00:42:01,079
But I think

953
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,599
this guidance and direction

954
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:05,079
is meant to help us make decisions,

955
00:42:05,199 --> 00:42:06,039
not to make decisions
for us.

956
00:42:07,199 --> 00:42:08,000
So I think,

957
00:42:08,880 --> 00:42:10,880
Shishan's reasoning might be

958
00:42:11,559 --> 00:42:12,519
that everyone
has the right to choose

959
00:42:13,199 --> 00:42:14,880
their own path in life.

960
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,400
And only by choosing for oneself

961
00:42:16,599 --> 00:42:17,599
and bearing the consequences,

962
00:42:18,199 --> 00:42:19,599
can one make this journey worthwhile.

963
00:42:21,679 --> 00:42:22,119
Anyway,

964
00:42:22,119 --> 00:42:23,840
I'm definitely going anyway.

965
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,599
I think preparing from now on

966
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:26,880
isn't too late.

967
00:42:27,679 --> 00:42:28,480
Mr. Xu,

968
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:30,320
just help me get

969
00:42:30,320 --> 00:42:31,360
my ID card back,

970
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:32,599
okay?

971
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:36,039
I believe you're well aware

972
00:42:36,559 --> 00:42:38,239
that reporting the ID card lost and getting a replacement

973
00:42:38,239 --> 00:42:39,360
would be much faster

974
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:40,280
than going to court.

975
00:42:41,880 --> 00:42:43,679
So what you really want, is it the ID card,

976
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:46,079
or is it your family's support?

977
00:42:53,039 --> 00:42:53,719
Shishan,

978
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:56,000
if you don't even have the courage

979
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,679
to face your father,

980
00:42:58,320 --> 00:42:59,199
how can you make

981
00:42:59,199 --> 00:43:00,480
your father believe

982
00:43:00,639 --> 00:43:02,480
that you have the courage to face

983
00:43:02,960 --> 00:43:04,480
the unforeseen difficulties in the future?

984
00:43:12,559 --> 00:43:13,480
I understand.

985
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:15,159
Mr. Xu.

986
00:43:22,719 --> 00:43:23,760
[Getting along with others]

987
00:43:24,079 --> 00:43:25,440
[requires remembering to put oneself in the other's shoes.]

988
00:43:26,280 --> 00:43:27,079
[Sometimes,]

989
00:43:27,559 --> 00:43:28,679
[what one thinks is care]

990
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:31,000
[might be seen by the other as control.]

991
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:33,920
[What one thinks is chasing a dream]

992
00:43:34,519 --> 00:43:36,159
[might be seen by the other as nonsense.]

993
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:38,559
[What one thinks is social suicide]

994
00:43:39,639 --> 00:43:41,280
[might be seen as adorable by the other .]

995
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:43,320
Have you had dinner?
